  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Architectural Site Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Descriptions</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Technical Implementation: </strong>Interpret, explain, and implement architectural blueprints, structural drawings, and technical specifications accurately on-site.</li><li><strong>Site Supervision & Management: </strong>Manage day-to-day operations, including scheduling, worker deployment, and coordinating subcontractors, suppliers, and consultants.</li><li><strong>Quality Control (QA/QC): </strong>Inspect work in progress, verify materials, and ensure all construction meets safety regulations (e.g., WSH Act) and design standards.</li><li><strong>Progress Tracking & Reporting: </strong>Monitor project timelines and budgets, identifying potential delays or issues to resolve them proactively.</li><li><strong>Documentation: </strong>Maintain detailed records, including daily site reports, material management, and project variations.</li><li><strong>Coordination: </strong>Liaise with architects, project managers, and clients to align construction with design intent. </li><li><strong>Ad-hoc Duties:</strong> Perform any other duties or tasks as assigned.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree in Civil Engineering, Architectural Engineering, or related field.</li><li>Minimum of 3 years of site supervision experience, preferably with knowledge of building materials and construction methods.</li><li>Proficiency in AutoCAD and other technical software.</li><li>Strong knowledge of local building regulations and safety compliance.</li><li>Ability to read and interpret complex architectural and structural drawings. </li><li>Self-motivated, able to work independently, meet tight deadlines, and proactively solve problems</li><li>Excellent organizational and communication skills to manage on-site logistics effectively.</li></ul>",
